{"id":"266516649_Spurious_Poles_in_Diagonal_Rational_Approximation","abstract":"Any function f meromorphic in C admits fast rational approximation. That is, if K is a compact set in which f is analytic, there exist rational functions R\nn\nof type (n,n),n ≥ 1, such that $$\\mathop {\\lim }\\limits_{n \\to \\infty } \\left\\| {f - {R_n}} \\right\\|_{{L_\\infty }(K)}^{1/n} = 0$$. More generally, any function f defined on an open set U, and admitting such approximation on a compact K ⊂ U with positive logarithmic capacity, is said to belong to the Gonchar-Walsh Class on U. We discuss at an introductory, non-technical, level, the problem of spurious poles for diagonal and sectorial sequences of rational approximants to functions in the Gonchar-Walsh class. In particular, we concentrate on some recent positive results on the distribution of poles, and some of their consequences.","authors":["D.s. Lubinsky"],"meta":["January 1992","DOI:10.1007/978-1-4612-2966-7_8"],"references":["303490371_Best_rational_approximations_of_entire_functions_whose_Maclaurin_series_coefficients_decrease_rapidly_and_smoothly","238869345_Pade_Tables_of_a_Class_of_Entire_Functions","226720048_Distribution_of_poles_of_diagonal_rational_approximants_to_functions_of_fast_rational_approximability","226513517_On_the_zeros_and_poles_of_Pad_approximants_toe_z_III","321522979_Die_Lehre_von_den_Kettenbruchen","316271033_Die_Lehre_von_den_Kettenbruchen","305005899_The_convergence_of_rational_functions_of_best_approximation_to_the_exponential_function_II","274647980_Analytic_Function_Theory_I","268709079_Erratum_'On_the_zeros_and_poles_of_Pade_approximants_to_e_z_'","268637476_The_Pade_tables_and_continued_fractions_generated_by_totally_positive_sequences","265699250_Analytic_function_theory_Vol_II","264959589_The_Essentials_of_Pade_Approximants","256587086_When_does_fz_have_a_regular_C-fraction_expansion_or_a_normal_Pade_table","252408167_The_Distribution_of_Poles_of_Rational_Functions_of_best_Approximatio